Reference-contexts: When considering biological issues involving ensembles of billions of "local" cell types, each developed from and functioning according to a single, shared, "global" genome and evaluated in terms of the "fitness" of the single resulting organism, the use of CA as a model of such "emergent" computations is especially appropriate <ref> [1] </ref>. A canonical example of such an emergent computation is to use a locally-specified CA to determine the global density of bits in an initial state configuration.
