Reference-contexts: In what follows, we will assume for convenience that if n is the size of the one-dimensional lattice, n is not an integer. The best known solution to this problem for = 1=2 is the GKL rule <ref> [2] </ref>. The basic strategy taken by GKL can be viewed as consolidating regions of local homogeneity, and sending 'signals' to ambiguous regions. Solid blocks of 0's or 1's convert adjacent undecided areas to their own state.
